# =============================================================
# .gitignore for engineering-apps
# =============================================================
# Anything matching the patterns below will NOT be committed
# to git, so it can never be accidentally pushed to a public
# repo. Add new patterns here whenever you want to keep
# something local-only.
# =============================================================

# --- macOS ---
.DS_Store
._*

# --- Python cache ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# --- IDE / local tooling ---
.claude/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.iml

# --- Backups & zips (store locally, never in repo) ---
GITHUB BACKUP ZIP FILE/
*.zip
*.zip.backup
*.bak

# --- Logs ---
*.log

# --- Office / temp / OS junk ---
~$*
Thumbs.db
.AppleDouble

# =============================================================
# Client / project work — keep all real project files OUT
# =============================================================
# These patterns make sure no actual BT client deliverables
# (drawings, project files, model exports, photos) ever land
# in this repo by accident, even if you forget.

# Folders that hold project work (case-insensitive, anywhere
# in the tree). Adjust naming convention as needed.
**/Structural Drawings/
**/Client Drawings/
**/Project Files/
**/Inspections/

# Large engineering project file types
*.btproject
*.dwg
*.dxf.bak
*.rvt
*.ifc
*.skp
*.3dm
*.stp
*.step
*.iges
*.igs

# Site photos / scans that shouldn't be public
**/Site Photos/
**/Inspection Photos/

# Scratch directories used by tools
.btinspect_scratch/
**/scratch/

# =============================================================
# Local config / secrets — never commit these
# =============================================================
.env
.env.*
*.secret
*secrets*
config.local.*
api-keys.*
